<subSubSection id="C30F32F2DF1DFFE31EBE89B82DAEFDFF" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1DFFE31EBE89B82F4EFE66" blockId="26.[211,309,391,415]" box="[211,309,391,415]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431">
<emphasis id="B961BD6BDF1DFFE31EBE89B82F4EFE66" box="[211,309,391,415]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA6179DF1DFFE31EBE89912DAEFDFF" blockId="26.[211,1172,430,518]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431">
This species is endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F30221E9DF1DFFE31C7E89912C11FE3F" box="[531,618,430,454]" name="Taiwan" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
. According to the original description and the redescription (
<bibRefCitation id="EF841C88DF1DFFE31F1989F12F80FE1F" author="Chujo M" box="[372,507,462,486]" pageId="26" pageNumber="1431" pagination="32 - 49" refId="ref12586" refString="Chujo M. 1952. A taxonomic study on the Chrysomelidae (Insecta-Coleoptera) from Formosa. Part V Subfamily Clytrinae (1). Tech Bull Kagawa Agric Coll. 4: 32 - 49." type="journal article" year="1952">Chûjô 1952</bibRefCitation>
), it can be easily recognized by the entirely yellowish brown pronotum and the black elytron with two yellowish brown markings.
</paragraph>
